data.description: New roof installed before closing or $13,000 cash back to buyer at closing for closing costs or to buy down Buyer’s rate. This property is across from golf course and country club. It offers wide street, spaces between houses, and extended driveway with space to build a circular driveway, large fenced back yard including shed with plenty of room to build a pool if so desire. The property is close to major highways 30 minutes from downtown Orlando, and 30 minutes from Daytona beach, 3-5 minutes from shopping center, movie theater, hospital, Amazon, and more. The interior of the home is split designed master separate from the other bedrooms. It is a lovely floor plan. The home has laminate floors in the living areas, hallway, and kitchen with tiles in the bedrooms and bathrooms. At the entry of the home there is a direct view to the family room; to the left of the entry way is the living room and formal dining room with high cathedral ceilings with left of dining room master bedroom/bath with patio door to the enclosed patio with backyard views and right of dining room is kitchen; back to entry walk directly from hallway enter the family room with ally kitchen to the left and kitchenette to the right open to family room; further right from kitchenette is 2 bedrooms with 1 bathroom in between the two rooms; far left side of the family room is double glass door to the enclosed patio with comfortable sitting/play area and backyard views; and back at entry right side of hallway is a 2 car garage. There are many updates to property and updated to be completed: Septic replaced 2015, interior paint 2022, cabinets and exterior paint completed in early part of 2021, to be replaced new water heater prior to closing. To top it all off this home has great value since the enclosed patio is not included in the heated sqft so once being forced AC/ heating the value will be even greater. Please note the disclaimer stating the room dimensions may be off and the heated sqft was not measured by us. We relied on the public records measurement hence we recommend buyers to measure the sqft and room dimensions.
